Meet <b>Brianna</b>, our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>Brianna has been holding it down at her comfortable <a href='/home/?user=bbrownw12'>20177-B Twilight Lane</a> home in Golden Valley, since June 27th, 2007.<br><br>Brianna's tenure in Millsberry is coming up on two years, and she's managed to rack up quite the honors during this time. She's received trophies for the Peabody Park Clean Up, Galactic Defender, Sudoku, Kai's Surfari, and Bumper Boats.<br><br>And she's been very happy in the Golden Valley neighborhood. It's located just south of the city proper, and boasts some of the most scenic locations in the area. Some say the commute to Millsberry is part of its charm.<br><br>Brianna describes herself as friendly, generous, and knowledgeable. So don't be surprised if she gives you a high five and then explains the origin of the gesture!<br><br>Her interests include singing, music, and animals. Sounds like she could very well serenade a snake. How charming.<br><br>If you're looking for Brianna, your best bet is to check the Ice Cream Parlor, the Arcade, or maybe the Amusement Park. <br><br>And, when you see her, make sure you give Brianna a pat on the back, to thank her for being such an outstanding citizen!<br></div>
